    • Method Detail

      • createObjectFromClass

        public static <T> T createObjectFromClass(java.lang.String className)

        This method loads a given class and creates an instance of it by invoking the class' default constructor. It is provided to shield calling applications from the need to explicitly handle the exceptions raised in the reflections API. However, note that this method will fail with a runtime error if an exception is thrown by the reflections API during the operation.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type defined by the class, and, consequently, the return type of this method.
        Parameters:
        className - The name of the class for which an instance is to be created
        Returns:
        A new instance of the specified class
        Throws:
        Latency4JException - If an exception is thrown by the underlying reflections API in the course of the operation.

      • isValidLong

        public static boolean isValidLong(java.lang.String candidateString)
        This method tests if the specified text is a valid Long. Put differently, it tests of the string can be used to obtain a long by calling the toLongValue(String) method.
        Parameters:
        candidateString - The string to test. Note that the string can be suffixed with the qualifier 'L' to differentiate it from an int.
        Returns:
        True if the String is a valid long, else it returns False

      • isValidBoolean

        public static boolean isValidBoolean(java.lang.String candidateString)
        Tests if the specified string is a valid boolean. This condition is satisfied if the supplied string is equivalent to either of the string literals "true" or "false", irrespective of case.
        Parameters:
        candidateString - The candidate string to test.
        Returns:
        True if the string is a valid boolean, and False otherwise.
